{"filePath":"examples/source/1.components/amp-image-lightbox.html","source":"<!--\n  ## Introduction\n\n  The [`amp-image-lightbox`](/amp-dev/documentation/components/reference/amp-image-lightbox-v0.1.md) component allows the user to expand an image to fill the viewport.\n--><!-- -->\n<!doctype html>\n<html ⚡4email>\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <script async src=\"https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0.js\"></script>\n  <!-- ## Setup -->\n  <!-- Import the amp-image-lightbox component in the header -->\n  <script async custom-element=\"amp-image-lightbox\" src=\"https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0/amp-image-lightbox-0.1.js\"></script>\n  <style amp4email-boilerplate>body{visibility:hidden}</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <!-- ## Basic usage -->\n  <!--\n    The `amp-image-lightbox` is activated using the `on` action on an `amp-img` element referencing the lightbox element's ID.\n  -->\n  <div>\n    <amp-img on=\"tap:lightbox1\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/static/samples/img/Border_Collie.jpg\" alt=\"Picture of a dog\" title=\"Picture of a dog, view in lightbox\" layout=\"responsive\" width=\"300\" height=\"246\"></amp-img>\n    <amp-image-lightbox id=\"lightbox1\" layout=\"nodisplay\"></amp-image-lightbox>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- ## Multi image support -->\n  <!--\n    It is even possible to show different images in the same `amp-image-lightbox`. Here is another image using the same lightbox.\n  -->\n  <amp-img on=\"tap:lightbox1\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/static/samples/img/Hovawart.jpg\" alt=\"Picture of a dog\" title=\"Picture of a dog, view in lightbox\" layout=\"responsive\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\"></amp-img>\n\n  <!-- ## Caption: figcaption -->\n  <!--\n    The amp-image-lightbox also can optionally display a caption for the image at the bottom of the viewport. This can either be the contents of the `<figcaption>` element when the image is in the figure tag...\n  -->\n  <figure>\n    <amp-img on=\"tap:lightbox1\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/static/samples/img/Border_Collie.jpg\" alt=\"Picture of a dog\" title=\"Picture of a dog, view in lightbox\" layout=\"responsive\" width=\"300\" height=\"246\"></amp-img>\n    <figcaption>Border Collie.</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n\n  <!-- ## Caption: aria-describedby -->\n  <!--\n    ... or the contents of the element whose ID is specified by the image's <code>aria-describedby</code> attribute.\n  -->\n  <div>\n    <amp-img on=\"tap:lightbox1\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-describedby=\"imageDescription\" alt=\"Picture of a dog\" title=\"Picture of a dog, view in lightbox\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/static/samples/img/Border_Collie.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"246\"></amp-img>\n    <div id=\"imageDescription\">\n      This is a border collie.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</body></html>","document":{"sections":[{"doc_":"\n## Introduction\n\nThe [`amp-image-lightbox`](/amp-dev/documentation/components/reference/amp-image-lightbox-v0.1.md) component allows the user to expand an image to fill the viewport.\n\n","code":"","preview":"","inBody":false,"id":0,"cachedMarkedDoc":"<h2 id=\"introduction\" class=\"www-heading pb4 mb2 relative h3\">Introduction</h2><p class=\"mb2 px1\">The <a href=\"/amp-dev/documentation/components/reference/amp-image-lightbox-v0.1.md\"><code>amp-image-lightbox</code></a> component allows the user to expand an image to fill the viewport.</p>","isLastSection":false,"isFirstSection":true,"commentOffset":0,"codeOffset":0,"headings":[{"id":"introduction","name":"Introduction"}],"storyPageId":"","currentHint":"","hints":[],"filters":null,"normalizedDoc_":"\n## Introduction\n\nThe [`amp-image-lightbox`](/amp-dev/documentation/components/reference/amp-image-lightbox-v0.1.md) component allows the user to expand an image to fill the viewport.\n\n"},{"doc_":"\n","code":"<!doctype html>\n<html ⚡4email>\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <script async src=\"https://cdn.ampproject.org/v0